OS2 // WARP.title: "Cloying Well-Dressed Numbers for Rubric", éditiones OPUS, OGG et ALAC, ca. 1988
OS2 // WARP.about:
BEWARE! Bandcamp won't let you listen to this marvelous music in OPUS as it was first intended when the seed for it was planted and nourished. This—a terrible blight, I may say—, if listened in any of the wrongful formats, may and can curse you and the next generations of your family for many and many years. This is hilarious. You are a fool! It is stated in the titles: éditiones OPUS, OGG et ALAC. Three formats, all stated for you, an insolent imbecile, and yet you favor the Devil's Work. FLAC? What is this? WAV? Such inefficiency! MP3? Such lack of the refinement we need in this country, take your hands of Kaaza, Limewire and Napster away from my groin! Furthermore, to convert this music to OPUS from a copy in any of the wrongful, dastardly formats—naught but an idiotic errand need not be run—is a disaster. The poison, it is spreading, a bubonic plague of losslessness. You hear your ears pinched by details that one's not had to witness from the inception of the work! And in the hereafter, black mold is subsuming your skin. This is a merriment for me, much schadenfreude you brought me, thinking Opus is ever ignorable! A thousand more years of slow horrific death to you!
— The author dearly, and with no jest,
with sincerity in His contentment in the direction of Yours,
Pierre Häagen-Dazs
OS2 // WARP.credits:
released July 28, 2022
Music by Pierre Häagen-Dazs—my name is not related to the ice cream maker, this is a different Häagen, the name of my father, a gentleman clockmaker he is, and Dazs, the name of my mother, a beautiful woman, elegant, well-endowed. Cover art by my dearest friend and indeed, deep confidante in an insurmountable time, Yannic Qiu.

OS2 // WARP.about:
download at  archive.org/details/cylces-4
once the .wav has been downloaded, change the extension to .txt and open in a text editor. delete everything up until the first character after the sentence "delete everything up until this point" which is surrounded by a large amount of space. change the file extension to .zip and extract an .mp3, which should be 2 minutes and thirteen seconds in length.

OS2 // WARP.title: cylces 5
OS2 // WARP.about:
download at  archive.org/details/cylces-5
cylces 5 is a password protected disk image file. upon entering the password, extract a 4 minute, 41 second .mp3.

OS2 // WARP.title: cylces 6
OS2 // WARP.about:
download at  archive.org/details/cylces-6
cylces 6 is an 11 minute, 30 second .mp3. to extract it, download the .zip file, extract the .wav, change its extension to .zip, and enter the password to the .zip.

OS2 // WARP.title: cylces 7
OS2 // WARP.about:
download at  archive.org/details/cylces-7
cylces 7 is a .zip, which contains an .mp3. change the mp3's extension to .zip, and enter the password to extract another .mp3. change this file's extension to .zip, and enter another password to extract another file. so on, until finally you will have extracted a 2 hour, 29 minute, 46 second .mp3.

OS2 // WARP.title: cylces 8
OS2 // WARP.about:
download at  archive.org/details/cylces-8
cylces 8 contains no passwords, but it will take some work to extract. expanding the .zip will reveal two .mp3's, each of which is a .zip in disguise containing two more .mp3's, which are also .zips in disguise containing two more .zips disguised as .mp3's, each of which contain two .mp3's. only one .mp3 of the sixteen will work, though. it is 3 hours, 36 minutes and 45 seconds long.
